item.description:
Summer is here and our tennis matches are in full swing! Join players of all levels as we play some games of Tennis. We will do our best to match players of similar skill levels to keep the games competitive yet fun. We are here to have fun, get to know each other and play tennis.

Tonight's Tennis Session is all about playing! If you would like more of an Open Tennis set-up in which you can play or just rally please let us know. Tonight we are playing tennis, whether it be singles or doubles or round-robin play.

*Who: Anyone who is able to play games of Tennis. (All levels - Beginners, Advanced Beginners, Intermediate and Advanced Players)
*What: A summer night of tennis, a great exercise!
*When: Tuesday, August 11th @ 6-8pm
*Where: Braintree High School
*Why: Tennis is a fun and great form of exercise!


Tuesday Night Tennis!
Tuesday, August 11th @ 6-8pm
Braintree High School Tennis Courts
128 Town Street
Braintree, MA 02184


*Meeting Place: At the tennis courts entrance nearest the backboards.

*Alternate Meeting Place: Look for us on one of the courts.

*Event Organizer(s): Chris (2008 & 2009 AM)

*Cost: $2/Member, $3/Guest, Annual Members are Free

*Min/Max: Minimum of 6 Yes RSVPs by 4pm on Friday, August 7th and 2 Co-Organizers. There is no max.

*Guests: Welcome! Up to 2 per member.

*RSVP Deadline: 12:30pm on Tuesday, August 11th

*Please Note in your RSVP Comments your anticipated arrival time and level of play.

In Case of Inclement Weather:
If it is raining the event will be cancelled. Heavy rains on Tuesday will cancel. **Please check back here (or the Talk About It section below) for an update on weather conditions.**

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Directions are posted on the "Directions to Frequently Used Venues" Discussion Thread on the Message Board.
item.how_to_find_us: We'll either be on the courts or at the entrance nearest the practice boards.
